(firstQuint)A Prospective Study of a New Device for Monitoring Cerebral Oxygenation on Healthy Volunteers.

 Cerebral oxygenation monitoring is an innovative way to monitoring cardiac surgery patients intraoperatively to reduce the incidence of postoperative hypoxic side effects.

 There are a number of approved devices already in the market that have proved their effectivity.

.

